article.headline: Sacred Heart 81, Lafayette 70
article.story: FAIRFIELD, Conn. -- Corey Hassan scored 21 points to lead four Sacred Heart players in double-figure scoring, helping the Pioneers outlast Lafayette 81-70 on Saturday in the first-ever meeting between the two teams. Chauncey Hardy scored 17, Ryan Litke 14 and Liam Potter 10 for the Pioneers (2-0), who went 11-for-17 from beyond the arc (64.7 percent). Litke hit four 3-pointers, while Hassan and Hardy had three apiece. The Pioneers trailed the Leopards (1-1) 36-34 at halftime, but Sacred Heart went on a 23-8 run midway through the second half to take the lead for good. Litke scored 11 points, including going 3-for-3 from beyond the arc, during the spree. Sacred Heart outscored Lafayette 47-34 in the second half. Ryan Willen scored 14 points to pace the Leopards and Jared Mintz added 12. The Pioneers outrebounded the Leopards 36-27.
